definition: (onom.) ting-a-ling (in compounds such as 玎玲 or 玲瓏|玲珑)/tinkling of gem-pendants
to scrape the meat from bones/to pick (teeth etc)/to weed out

sentences.english: Jenny was so smart that I was afraid she would laugh at me.
sentences.chinese: 詹妮玲瓏剔透，我真擔心自己會被她笑話。

sentences.english: Paper cut in South China is well known for its exquisite, elegant, realistic style.
sentences.chinese: 而南方剪紙玲瓏剔透嚴整優雅，以寫實風格著稱。
